Leaflet for R

  • Show All Code
  • Hide All Code
  • View Source
Modified

September 17, 2023

1 はじめに

  • Leaflet for Rの学習ノートです
  • API reference
  • すべてではなく気になった部分だけを記録しています
  • albersusaパッケージはここインストールしています

2 Features

  • Interactive panning/zooming
  • Compose maps using arbitrary combinations of:
    • Map tiles
    • Markers
    • Polygons
    • Lines
    • Popups
    • GeoJSON
  • Create maps right from the R console or RStudio
  • Embed maps in knitr/R Markdown documents and Shiny apps
  • Easily render spatial objects from the sp or sf packages, or data frames with latitude/longitude columns
  • Use map bounds and mouse events to drive Shiny logic
  • Display maps in non spherical mercator projections
  • Augment map features using chosen plugins from leaflet plugins repository

3 Basic Usage

Code 
library(here)
library(shiny)
library(leaflet)
library(leafem)
library(htmltools)
library(htmlwidgets)
library(rjson)
library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(stars)
library(glue)
library(knitr)

シンプルなポップアップの作成例. 埋め込みしないで, linkを貼るときにはheight = 100vhが良さそうである.

Code 

m <- 
    leaflet(
        width = "100%", 
        height = "50vh", 
    ) |> 
    addTiles() |> 
    addMarkers(
        lng = 139.6928976, 
        lat = 35.69023, 
        popup = "Tokyo Metropolytan Building"
    )

m

htmlデータの作成の作成はsaveWidgetを使う. htmltoolsのsave_htmlだとライブラリが別ファイルになるが, そのライブラリをQuartoのビルドで移動させるやり方がわからない. saveWidgetsなら1つのhtmlファイルになる.

Code 
cur_dir <- here("contents/website/leaflet4r")
saveWidget(m, file = here(cur_dir, "./basic_leaflet.html"))

出力したファイルのリンクの作成をおこなう.

3.1 文字列へのリンク

leaflet map

3.2 画像へのリンク

lightboxの効果はないのに注意すること.

3.3 GeoJSON

Code 
geojson <- "https://www.geospatial.jp/ckan/dataset/669fc4ff-317b-48cf-a43d-9340ff04ff18/resource/ccff82d4-2353-49e6-9845-371ee6d622de/download/biomasspowerstation42.geojson"
geojson <- "https://www.geospatial.jp/ckan/dataset/a4f2f167-1433-47ea-b7be-ce88660a30a2/resource/72f6ed4e-a68c-4082-a90f-dd7e5423d87a/download/p35_18_03.geojson"
x <- fromJSON(file = geojson)
y <- read_sf(geojson)
ytext <- 
    y %>%
    "st_geometry<-"(NULL) %>%
    transpose() %>%
    map( ~ glue("{names(.x)} = {.x}")) %>%
    map_chr(~ str_c(.x, collapse = "<br/>"))
as_longstyle_htmltable <- function(data) {
    data %>%
        mutate(across(everything(), as.character)) %>%
        rowwise() %>%
        summarise(htmltbl = list(tibble(`属性` = names(cur_data()), `値` = flatten_chr(cur_data())))) %>%
        mutate(htmltbl = map(htmltbl, ~ kable(.x, format = "html"))) %>%
        mutate(htmltbl = map(htmltbl, ~ str_replace(.x, "<table>", "<table style='border: solid 1px #f8f8f8;border-collapse:collapse;height:auto;max-height:35vh;overflow-y:scroll'>"))) %>%
        mutate(htmltbl = map(htmltbl, ~ str_replace_all(.x, "<th style=\"text-align:left;\">", "<th style=\"text-align:center;background-color:black;color:white\">"))) %>%
        mutate(htmltbl = map(htmltbl, ~ str_replace_all(.x, "<tr>", "<tr style='border: solid 1px #f8f8f8;'>"))) %>%
        mutate(htmltbl = map(htmltbl, ~ str_replace_all(.x, "<td style=\"text-align:left;\">", "<td style=\"text-align:left;padding:0.5em\">")))
}

yattr      <- "st_geometry<-"(y, NULL)
ytabletext <- as_longstyle_htmltable(yattr)
#> Warning: There was 1 warning in `summarise()`.
#> ℹ In argument: `htmltbl = list(tibble(属性 = names(cur_data()), 値 =
#>   flatten_chr(cur_data())))`.
#> ℹ In row 1.
#> Caused by warning:
#> ! `cur_data()` was deprecated in dplyr 1.1.0.
#> ℹ Please use `pick()` instead.


rm(m)
m <- 
    leaflet(
        width = "100%",
        height = "800"
    ) %>%
    addTiles(urlTemplate = "https://cyberjapandata.gsi.go.jp/xyz/seamlessphoto/{z}/{x}/{y}.jpg", group = "空中写真", layerId = "photo") %>%
    addTiles(urlTemplate = "http://cyberjapandata.gsi.go.jp/xyz/std/{z}/{x}/{y}.png", group = "標準地図", layerId = "gsi") %>%
    addTiles(urlTemplate = "https://tile.geospatial.jp/ks-shinsuisoutei/A31-19_83_SHP_tile/{z}/{x}/{y}.png", group = "MLIT") %>%
    addFeatures(data = st_geometry(y), popup = ytabletext$htmltbl, group = "new") %>%
    addLayersControl(
        baseGroup     = c("標準地図", "空中写真"), 
        overlayGroups = c("new", "MLIT")
    )
    

m %>%
    addFeatures(data = st_geometry(y), popup = ytabletext$htmltbl, group = "new2") %>%
    addLayersControl(
        baseGroup     = c("標準地図", "空中写真"), 
        overlayGroups = c("new", "new2")
    )

3.4 GeoTiff

Code 
library(stars)
library(leafem)

r <- read_stars(here(cur_dir, "data/DCWD_map.tif"))
leaflet() %>%
    addTiles(group = "OpenStreetMap") %>% 
    addStarsRGB(r)

3.5 GPS

Code 
library(leaflet)
library(leaflet.extras)

map <- leaflet() %>% addTiles()

map <- addControlGPS(
    map, 
    options = gpsOptions(
        position = "topleft", 
        activate = TRUE, 
        autoCenter = TRUE, 
        maxZoom = 10, 
        setView = TRUE
    )
)

activateGPS(map)

3.6 Vector tile

Code 
library(leaflet)
library(htmltools)

m <- leaflet() %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  setView(lng = 174.768, lat = -36.852, zoom = 10)

m_html <- as.character(m)

vector_tile_js <- "
L.vectorGrid.protobuf('https://cyberjapandata.gsi.go.jp/xyz/experimental_bvmap/{z}/{x}/{y}.pbf').addTo(map);
"

browsable(
  tagList(
    tags$head(tags$script(src = "https://unpkg.com/leaflet.vectorgrid/dist/Leaflet.VectorGrid.js")),
    HTML(m_html),
    tags$script(HTML(vector_tile_js))
  )
)

# はじめに

- [Leaflet for R](https://rstudio.github.io/leaflet/)の学習ノートです
- [API reference](https://web.archive.org/web/20220709131410/https://leafletjs.com/reference-1.3.4.html#map-option)
- すべてではなく気になった部分だけを記録しています
- albersusaパッケージは[ここ](https://github.com/hrbrmstr/albersusa)インストールしています



# Features

- Interactive panning/zooming
- Compose maps using arbitrary combinations of:
    - Map tiles
    - Markers
    - Polygons
    - Lines
    - Popups
    - GeoJSON
- Create maps right from the R console or RStudio
- Embed maps in knitr/R Markdown documents and Shiny apps
- Easily render spatial objects from the sp or sf packages, or data frames with latitude/longitude columns
- Use map bounds and mouse events to drive Shiny logic
- Display maps in non spherical mercator projections
- Augment map features using chosen plugins from leaflet plugins repository


# Basic Usage


```{r}
#| warning: false
#| message: false

library(here)
library(shiny)
library(leaflet)
library(leafem)
library(htmltools)
library(htmlwidgets)
library(rjson)
library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(stars)
library(glue)
library(knitr)
```



シンプルなポップアップの作成例. 
埋め込みしないで, linkを貼るときには`height = 100vh`が良さそうである. 


```{r}
m <- 
    leaflet(
        width = "100%", 
        height = "50vh", 
    ) |> 
    addTiles() |> 
    addMarkers(
        lng = 139.6928976, 
        lat = 35.69023, 
        popup = "Tokyo Metropolytan Building"
    )

m
```

htmlデータの作成の作成は`saveWidget`を使う. 
htmltoolsのsave_htmlだとライブラリが別ファイルになるが, 
そのライブラリをQuartoのビルドで移動させるやり方がわからない. 
saveWidgetsなら1つのhtmlファイルになる. 


```{r}
cur_dir <- here("contents/website/leaflet4r")
saveWidget(m, file = here(cur_dir, "./basic_leaflet.html"))
```

出力したファイルのリンクの作成をおこなう.

## GPS

```{r}
library(leaflet)
library(leaflet.extras)

map <- leaflet() %>% addTiles()

map <- addControlGPS(
    map, 
    options = gpsOptions(
        position = "topleft", 
        activate = TRUE, 
        autoCenter = TRUE, 
        maxZoom = 10, 
        setView = TRUE
    )
)

activateGPS(map)
```

## Vector tile

```{r eval=FALSE}
library(leaflet)
library(htmltools)

m <- leaflet() %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  setView(lng = 174.768, lat = -36.852, zoom = 10)

m_html <- as.character(m)

vector_tile_js <- "
L.vectorGrid.protobuf('https://cyberjapandata.gsi.go.jp/xyz/experimental_bvmap/{z}/{x}/{y}.pbf').addTo(map);
"

browsable(
  tagList(
    tags$head(tags$script(src = "https://unpkg.com/leaflet.vectorgrid/dist/Leaflet.VectorGrid.js")),
    HTML(m_html),
    tags$script(HTML(vector_tile_js))
  )
)

```
